5. Enforcement, Blacklisting & Technical Measures
────────────────────────────────────────
5.1 Non-Compliance  
Failure to obtain a required license, ignoring licensing contact, or
continuing unauthorized use constitutes a material breach of this
Agreement.

5.2 Blacklisting  
BlackRift Studios reserves the right to blacklist any non-compliant
distribution, project, or usage context.

5.3 Technical Enforcement  
BlackRift Studios may implement technical measures to restrict, disable,
or prevent the Software from functioning when used in violation of this
Agreement. Such measures may include, but are not limited to:

    - Partial or complete functional disablement
    - Refusal to operate in unauthorized environments
    - Controlled application or game termination at startup or runtime,
      accompanied by a clear message or log indicating license violation
      or blacklist status

5.4 Anti-Circumvention  
Any attempt to bypass, remove, or interfere with licensing checks,
blacklisting systems, or enforcement mechanisms is strictly prohibited.

